# d.lower.sdd

Scope: Latin lowercase d prototype glyph.

## Must

- Establish a lowercase ascender-gated form that pairs cleanly with `n.lower.sdd` stem logic.
- Derive bowl width and stroke logic from `o.lower.sdd` without copying it directly.
- Keep the stem-counter relationship stable when paired with straight and round letters.
- Define the first lowercase ascender rhythm for later `h` and potential `p/b/q` decisions.

## Must not

- Introduce a descender or any lower-side projection in Phase 1.
- Reinterpret baseline or x-height from this glyph; reuse family defaults from `masters/regular.sdd`.
- Use this glyph to solve spacing problems that should be addressed in `metrics/spacing.sdd`.

## Owns

- Lowercase ascender-and-bowl interface.
- Sidebearing contract for stem-to-round transitions (`dn`, `do`, `od`, `ad`).
- First explicit prototype for ascender carry in Phase 1 prototype set.

## Depends on

- `n.lower.sdd`
- `o.lower.sdd`
- `../../design-principles.sdd`
- `../../masters/regular.sdd`
- `../../metrics/spacing.sdd`

## Forbids

- Descender-like bowls.
- A bowl that closes with blunt optical weight at the top while appearing lighter at the entry.
- Any asymmetry that makes `dd` or `od` rhythm feel unbalanced.

## Done when

- d works in `ad`, `da`, `dd`, `do`, `od`, `de`, and `non`-style transitions without kerning.
- Human review accepts `d` as a stable ascender model for future `b/p/q` family members.
- The ascender-bowl join is visually consistent with `h.lower.sdd` and does not collapse sidebearings in `proof/strings.txt`.